{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ParallaxLayer\/motionMirroring","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"title":"motionMirroring","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"motionMirroring","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Vector2","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot7Vector2V"}],"modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"property","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot13ParallaxLayerC15motionMirroringAA7Vector2Vvp"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ParallaxLayer"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"motionMirroring"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Vector2","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Vector2","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot7Vector2V"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want the repetition to pixel-perfect match a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Texture2D"},{"text":" displayed by a child node, you should account for any scale applied to the texture when defining this interval. For example, if you use a child ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Sprite2D"},{"type":"text","text":" scaled to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0.5"},{"text":" to display a 600x600 texture, and want this sprite to be repeated continuously horizontally, you should set the mirroring to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Vector2(300, 0)"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If the length of the viewport axis is bigger than twice the repeated axis size, it will not repeat infinitely, as the parallax layer only draws 2 instances of the layer at any given time. The visibility window is calculated from the parent ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ParallaxBackground","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"‘s position, not the layer’s own position. So, if you use mirroring, "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"do not"}]},{"text":" change the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ParallaxLayer","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" position relative to its parent. Instead, if you need to adjust the background’s position, set the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CanvasLayer\/offset","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" property in the parent ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ParallaxBackground","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Despite the name, the layer will not be mirrored, it will only be repeated.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/parallaxlayer\/motionmirroring"]}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The interval, in pixels, at which the "